---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHeader from "../components/PageHeader.astro";
import StageInitialConditions from "../components/story/StageInitialConditions.astro";

const stages = [
  { n: 1, name: "Initial conditions", tag: "You can't study a cluster until you can build one." },
  { n: 2, name: "Dynamics", tag: "Stars pull on each other. Gravity moves them." },
  { n: 3, name: "Observables", tag: "We never see masses — only light." },
  { n: 4, name: "Inference", tag: "Run it backwards: what could the light ever tell us?" },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Modeling a star cluster, from first principles — Anna Rosen"
  description="An interactive, first-principles walk through how a differentiable model builds a star cluster — from initial conditions to what its light can reveal."
  path="/model-path"
>
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="Explore · from first principles"
    title="How we model a star cluster"
    lede="My group builds star clusters inside a computer — from the ground up — so we can ask what their light could ever tell us. Here is that path, one honest step at a time. Nothing below assumes you've seen it before."
  />

  <div class="mp wrap">
    <ol class="mp__map" role="list" aria-label="The model path">
      {
        stages.map((s) => (
          <li class="mp__step">
            <span class="mp__num">{String(s.n).padStart(2, "0")}</span>
            <span class="mp__name">{s.name}</span>
            <span class="mp__tag">{s.tag}</span>
          </li>
        ))
      }
    </ol>

    <section class="mp__section" aria-labelledby="step-1">
      <p class="mp__kicker">Step 01 · Initial conditions</p>
      <h2 id="step-1" class="mp__h2">First, make a cluster</h2>
      <div class="mp__prose prose">
        <p>
          A star cluster is just a crowd of stars that formed together. To model
          one, the first question is deceptively simple: <em>how many stars, how
          heavy is each, and where do they sit?</em>
        </p>
        <p>
          Nature answers the "how heavy" part with a remarkably consistent rule
          called the <strong>initial mass function</strong> (IMF): it makes
          <em>many</em> small stars and only a rare <em>few</em> massive ones.
          Below, each star is drawn from that rule — a broken power law measured
          across real clusters. Resample it, and watch: the crowd is always
          mostly faint red stars, with a scarce handful of brilliant blue giants.
          Those giants are rare, but they run the show — a theme you'll meet
          again in every step that follows.
        </p>
      </div>

      <StageInitialConditions />

      <p class="mp__aside">
        The masses come from the Kroupa (2001) IMF; each star's color follows its
        mass through a main-sequence temperature relation. Same code that draws
        the cluster on the homepage — here it's yours to poke.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mp__next">
      <p class="mp__kicker">Coming next</p>
      <h2 class="mp__h2">Then: let it evolve</h2>
      <p class="mp__prose prose">
        With a cluster in hand, the next steps set it in motion — gravity pulls
        the stars into orbits and ejects some entirely; the light we'd actually
        observe is projected onto the sky and blurred by noise; and finally we
        run the whole chain <em>backwards</em> to ask what that light could ever
        have told us about how the cluster was born. Those steps are on the way.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .mp {
    padding-block: var(--space-l) var(--space-3xl);
  }

  .mp__map {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(12rem, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-s);
    margin-block-end: var(--space-2xl);
  }
  .mp__step {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-3xs);
    padding: var(--space-s);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-m);
    background: var(--bg-deep);
  }
  .mp__num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--spec-teal) 65%, transparent);
  }
  .mp__name {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--step-0);
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .mp__tag {
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    color: var(--ink-dim);
  }

  .mp__section {
    padding-block-start: var(--space-l);
    border-block-start: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .mp__kicker {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wide);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--spec-teal-bright);
    margin-block-end: var(--space-2xs);
  }
  .mp__h2 {
    font-size: var(--step-3);
    margin-block-end: var(--space-m);
  }
  .mp__prose {
    color: var(--ink-soft);
  }
  .mp__prose p + p {
    margin-block-start: var(--space-s);
  }
  .mp__prose strong {
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .mp__aside {
    margin-block-start: var(--space-m);
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    max-inline-size: var(--width-prose);
  }
  .mp__next {
    margin-block-start: var(--space-2xl);
    padding-block-start: var(--space-l);
    border-block-start: 1px solid var(--border);
    opacity: 0.85;
  }
</style>
